1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,520
 So, what I'm about to say, I have a disclaimer,

2
00:00:03,520 --> 00:00:06,080
 I have the approval to say this.

3
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:08,280
 At least I told her I'm gonna say this.

4
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:10,280
 At least she heard it in Chinese already.

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:15,520
 So, my wife is really Wonder Woman.

6
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:22,800
 Because every day, at least three times or two times,

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,040
 she would ask, "I wonder where my phone is?"

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:31,840
 So, yeah, every day, like a couple of times.

9
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:36,040
 And I guess one of the things that we bonded over

10
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:38,400
 was actually forgetfulness.

11
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:41,680
 If you know me, some of you, you're visiting

12
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,200
 or you're new here, I have ADHD.

13
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:46,520
 So, one of the hallmark of people with ADHD,

14
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:48,040
 it's forgetfulness.

15
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:51,400
 On top of that, it's how messy my life could be.

16
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:55,160
 My desk, my room, my house.

17
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:58,920
 Well, thankfully, my wife is here to tidy up.

18
00:00:58,920 --> 00:01:01,320
 But my life is quite messy.

19
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:04,920
 When my messiness, it's coupled with my forgetfulness,

20
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:07,400
 that results in only one thing.

21
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:10,080
 I always misplace my stuff.

22
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:11,560
 I always couldn't find them.

23
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:15,160
 So, before I moved, before I got married,

24
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:17,400
 my sister is here, so she would know.

25
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:19,480
 I'm constantly running around the house,

26
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:20,520
 finding, "Oh, where are my stuff?

27
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:21,800
 "Where are my stuff?

28
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,520
 "Where did something go?"

29
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:26,600
 But there was a period in my time, about a couple years ago,

30
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,480
 before I moved, before I got married,

31
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:31,360
 there was a period in my life

32
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:34,360
 where I would be looking for something

33
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,440
 and then I would be praying,

34
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,360
 "Okay, God, I don't know where my stuff went."

35
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:42,480
 And then, shortly, I would have this revelation.

36
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,840
 Sometimes it's like a picture in my head,

37
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:45,720
 where to look for it.

38
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:48,640
 Sometimes it's this idea God just dropped in my head.

39
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:50,400
 And so, I will find it.

40
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,400
 So, there was one day I was, again,

41
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,720
 looking for my misplaced item.

42
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:59,320
 And I was just looking everywhere,

43
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:02,080
 in drawers, in boxes, or bags,

44
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,720
 and I've been looking everywhere,

45
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:06,320
 like I leave no stone unturned,

46
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,640
 that kind of desperate situation.

47
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:11,960
 And I could hear this voice in my head saying,

48
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,240
 "Why don't you just pray?

49
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:16,080
 "You're just one prayer away from finding it."

50
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:19,640
 But, you know, I'm a huge fan of Sherlock Holmes.

51
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,800
 (audience laughing)

52
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:25,200
 So, I am a little detective,

53
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:27,520
 like there's this detective inside of me.

54
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:32,320
 So, I was like, "No, I wanna try and find it by myself

55
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:35,520
 "because I have this detective spirit inside of me."

56
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:40,440
 So, I've been looking in different areas in my house.

57
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:44,080
 I think in the process, I made my house even more messy.

58
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,440
 Sorry to my family.

59
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:49,040
 And after a while, I was so exhausted.

60
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,600
 It's not just physically exhausted,

61
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,720
 it's the mental kind of exhaustion.

62
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:55,800
 I'm like, "I thought I could, I looked everywhere,

63
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,240
 "every place I could think of,

64
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:59,400
 "I tried to look and I couldn't find it."

65
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,240
 So, I was super exhausted.

66
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:04,000
 When I'm exhausted, I decide to go for a nap,

67
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
 or at least just lie down and rest.

68
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,320
 So, I walked to my bedroom,

69
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,920
 I was about to lie down on my bed,

70
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:13,200
 and as I was doing so, I was just, you know,

71
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,840
 mentally like praying in my head,

72
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:17,400
 "Okay, God, if you know where it is, please tell me."

73
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:20,600
 And I was lying down, and boom, literally,

74
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,080
 before my body hit the bed,

75
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,320
 there's this idea dropped into my head.

76
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:28,440
 Oh, there's this particular bag, this backpack,

77
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,360
 and in the front pocket of the backpack,

78
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,080
 have you looked there?

79
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,760
 This idea literally hit my head.

80
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:35,760
 I'm like, "No way, I barely, like,

81
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:38,680
 "my body barely hit the bed and I have to get up again."

82
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,240
 Like, those dance moves, you know?

83
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,480
 No, I can't do it, sorry.

84
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:45,800
 And then, so I went to the back,

85
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:49,160
 opened the front pocket, reached deeply, you know, inside,

86
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,760
 and ta-da, there it is.

87
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:54,160
 I found what I was looking for.

88
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:58,720
 So, to say the least, when it comes to lost and found,

89
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,560
 prayer has always been my last resort.

90
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:07,720
 I thought, "Come on, I can do it myself.

91
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,800
 "I'm a detective, I'm like Sherlock Holmes,

92
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,280
 "you know, I can handle it myself.

93
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:14,840
 "God, I got it, just let me find it, I can handle it."

94
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,840
 You okay?

95
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:20,080
 It's kind of like my daughters, you know,

96
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:22,800
 when it comes to buttoning their shirt, you know,

97
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,320
 or opening a bottle, or reaching something

98
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,000
 pretty high on the shelf,

99
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,360
 as long as they think they have the ability

100
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,600
 to do it themselves,

101
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,440
 daddy will always be the last resort.

102
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,960
 Right?

103
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:38,320
 Yeah, you're laughing, of course, you know, right?

104
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,720
 Yeah.

105
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:43,920
 So, whatever it is, daddy is always the last person

106
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,160
 she would come to because they think,

107
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,440
 "I can do it by myself."

108
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:51,320
 And if we zoom in a little bit on this idea,

109
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:53,120
 or on this mentality,

110
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:56,320
 and we see that at the core of this motivation,

111
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:59,960
 where it says, "I can do it, I wanna do it by myself,"

112
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:03,120
 this is the idea of competence.

113
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:06,200
 That I have the ability to get certain things done.

114
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,280
 And the drive for competence isn't, you know,

115
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,920
 inherently bad.

116
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,640
 You know, we learn stuff as a kid,

117
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:15,840
 as a fundamental human longing,

118
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,480
 that, you know, from childhood,

119
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:20,240
 we learn new languages, we master new skills,

120
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,560
 we learn to walk,

121
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:24,800
 and we learn to solve puzzles or other problems.

122
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,560
 It's because that this feeling,

123
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,160
 I wanna be able to do it,

124
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:31,160
 I wanna feel competent inside of me.

125
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,920
 The desire to master a new skill,

126
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,440
 or overcome challenges,

127
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,080
 it's deep within us,

128
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:40,000
 and it's not a bad thing at all.

129
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,520
 But, you know, when this natural desire,

130
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:47,000
 it's slowly, or a natural desire for competence,

131
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,880
 when it becomes an all-consuming idol,

132
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,120
 when we wanna feel our worth,

133
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,760
 when we wanna feel, you know, our identity

134
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,080
 from what we can do,

135
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:59,840
 or literally, in a town, in this city,

136
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,600
 it would be we are what we do.

137
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,560
 If we tie our identity, our self-worth,

138
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,960
 with our competence,

139
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,080
 when it becomes our idol,

140
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,760
 that's the problem.

141
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,960
 That's where the problem begins.

142
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,800
 We would unknowingly and slowly

143
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,760
 push God away to the side.

144
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:20,040
 You wanna push him slightly further away

145
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,880
 from the center, and we say,

146
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,320
 "Okay, God, just stay there.

147
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:26,040
 When I need you, I'll call you, all right?

148
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,520
 Just stay there.

149
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,600
 Grab a seat at the piano there.

150
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,720
 Just stay there, all right?

151
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,120
 I'll call you later."

152
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,360
 We slowly push God away,

153
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,840
 and we will start to believe

154
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:37,640
 that our identity, our self-worth,

155
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:40,480
 it's solely tied to what we can do,

156
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:43,280
 to our achievements, to our ability,

157
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:47,120
 you know, because I can handle it.

158
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:50,400
 In other words, we live in a world

159
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,880
 or culture that values competence

160
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,520
 over dependence,

161
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:59,000
 or should I say, perceived competence.

162
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,200
 We thought what we could do, all right?

163
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,480
 I believe this little story of mine

164
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,320
 points to a much deeper

165
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,240
 and a more pervasive problem

166
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,360
 for many of us as Christians.

167
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,680
 We live in a world that worships

168
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:15,120
 at the altar of competence.

169
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:18,600
 Yeah, we believe in Jesus, we follow Jesus,

170
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,960
 but at the same time,

171
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:23,000
 when it comes to our self-worth,

172
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,800
 when it comes to our value,

173
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,800
 when it comes to our identity,

174
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,920
 we're driven by the idea of competence.

175
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:32,480
 Our older daughter,

176
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:35,240
 she is in the third year of kindergarten,

177
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,080
 which means our family currently,

178
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:39,040
 it's going through a season

179
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,360
 of primary school interview,

180
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,960
 primary school application,

181
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,280
 and we're doing all that.

182
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:47,160
 And this whole process just reminded me

183
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:49,240
 of the struggle or the dilemma

184
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,600
 that we're all going through,

185
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,840
 or we're all facing.

186
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:54,960
 We have seen the endless toil

187
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:58,040
 or that stress that our next generation,

188
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:59,040
 they have to go through,

189
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,240
 like doing their homework until what,

190
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,960
 10, 10.30, 11 p.m. at night.

191
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,960
 We saw how difficult it is.

192
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:08,400
 We saw how much competition

193
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:10,600
 is destroying their confidence.

194
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,800
 We saw all that.

195
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,480
 And sometimes we're so sick

196
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:16,400
 and so tired of competition in our society

197
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,320
 that we wanna take them out of competition.

198
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,320
 But then sometimes,

199
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:22,400
 as we are looking through different schools,

200
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,240
 as we thought,

201
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,080
 oh, we don't want them to go

202
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,040
 through so much competition,

203
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,240
 so why don't we take them out to a place,

204
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,360
 to a happy school, to somewhere,

205
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,600
 it will be less stressful,

206
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,120
 it will be less competitive.

207
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,560
 But then this fear,

208
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:35,800
 just this fear is so real,

209
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,840
 it just speaks to us,

210
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,480
 what if, what if because we put them

211
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:42,400
 in an environment that is less competitive,

212
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,560
 they will be less competent?

213
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:49,320
 That that fear is so real in our head.

214
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,880
 And that's why there's a saying

215
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:54,400
 that you can take people out of competition,

216
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:58,880
 but it's very hard to take competition out of people.

217
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:00,400
 It's so real.

218
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:03,080
 And we're so afraid,

219
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:05,040
 on one hand, we don't want them

220
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,960
 to be in a competitive environment,

221
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,480
 but on the other hand,

222
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,520
 we're so afraid that if they're not

223
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,880
 in a competitive environment,

224
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:14,120
 they will not be competent.

225
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:17,120
 I think that reveals something deeper inside of us,

226
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:19,320
 that we believe competition

227
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,160
 is the only way to competence

228
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:24,240
 and competence is the only way to success.

229
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,040
 I think that's the belief.

230
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,600
 If there's a religion in this city,

231
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,440
 that would be it.

232
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:31,640
 That's what we believe in the city of Hong Kong,

233
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:35,120
 or probably in the wider Asia area as well.

234
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:38,400
 In Hong Kong or in many professional cultures,

235
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:41,600
 success is defined by what we can achieve

236
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,040
 through our own skills,

237
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:46,840
 our own intellect and our own effort.

238
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,560
 We are taught and encouraged

239
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,800
 to project an image of achieved competence,

240
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,960
 not immediate dependence.

241
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,840
 Let me say that again.

242
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,600
 We are encouraged,

243
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,560
 we are taught to project an image,

244
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:02,760
 a self image of our achieved competence

245
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:05,440
 instead of our immediate dependence.

246
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,120
 You don't want people to look at you

247
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:10,280
 and think you are dependent on anyone.

248
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,760
 That makes you look weak.

249
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:13,560
 That makes you look incompetent.

250
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:16,360
 That makes people don't wanna hire you.

251
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,520
 Why do I need to hire you

252
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:20,760
 and I need to hire someone for you to depend on?

253
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,040
 I don't wanna hire someone like that.

254
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,800
 I want someone who is independent.

255
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,160
 I want someone who can achieve everything by themselves.

256
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,800
 That's the culture we're in right now.

257
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:34,720
 And this, it's called the Babylonian view of success.

258
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,480
 The Bible often use Babylon,

259
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,640
 not just to refer to a historical city

260
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:41,400
 that existed on earth.

261
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,880
 It is also a very powerful symbol

262
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,320
 for a world system or its values,

263
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:49,760
 a system characterized by self-sufficiency,

264
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:54,760
 by human achievement and a rejection of divine authority.

265
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:57,920
 From Genesis all the way to Revelation,

266
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,960
 Babylon represents a culture

267
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:03,440
 that prioritize its own wisdom, power,

268
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:07,880
 its own glory, often in direct opposition to God's way.

269
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:13,400
 It embodies the human tendency to build kingdoms

